---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Work | Amid the Noise">
  <section class="section">
    <h1>Work</h1>
    <p>
      Selected systems work focused on decision-making, trust, and real-world constraints.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <article>
      <h2>Experience</h2>
      <p>
        A condensed view of roles across systems design, AI, and data-intensive environments.
        Full details are available on LinkedIn and in my résumé.
      </p>
      <div class="experience-list">
        <p><span class="role">Principal Product Designer (Independent)</span>, Amid the Noise<br/>2022–Present</p>
        <p><span class="role">Principal Product Designer</span>, Dremio<br/>2021–2022</p>
        <p><span class="role">UX Strategy & Intelligent Automation Lead (Principal)</span>, Automation Anywhere<br/>2020–2021</p>
        <p><span class="role">Lead Design Thinker, AI Enterprise Solutions</span>, Wells Fargo<br/>2019</p>
        <p><span class="role">Principal Product Designer (Entrepreneur-in-Residence)</span>, CA Technologies<br/>2017–2019</p>
        <p><span class="role">Product Design & Systems Innovation</span>, Netscape · Friendster · Yahoo · Autodesk · Evernote<br/>1996–2016</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <article>
      <h2>Case Studies</h2>
      <p>
        This section is being built to document applied work across product design, complex systems,
        and regulated environments. It will focus on how problems were framed, what decisions were
        made, and what changed as a result.
      </p>
      <p>
        The goal is not to recreate a résumé. It is to show how design thinking translates into
        operational clarity inside real systems.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <article>
      <h2>In Progress</h2>
      <p>
        The first case study is currently in development and will be published here shortly.
      </p>
      <p>
        Initial entries will focus on work involving trust, decision support, user experience in
        constrained environments, and systems where ambiguity carries real cost.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .experience-list p {
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .experience-list .role {
    font-weight: 500; /* softer than bold */
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }
</style>